00:51:40.730 --> 00:51:45.310 position:56%
I was wondering if you could say
something about the training process

00:51:45.310 --> 00:51:48.860
and particularly how
the shapes are created.

00:51:48.860 --> 00:51:53.110
&gt;&gt; Ann McClellan: Yes; the question
is how are the shapes created?

00:51:53.110 --> 00:51:55.310
And actually there are
several different ways.

00:51:55.310 --> 00:51:57.300
Sometimes -- most often
today they use wire.

00:51:57.300 --> 00:52:00.250 position:56%
They trim and then they help the
new growth by using wire to shape it

00:52:00.250 --> 00:52:03.110
in the way that they want it to go.

00:52:03.110 --> 00:52:07.470
Do you remember that wonderful
tree that Stephen showed you

00:52:07.470 --> 00:52:11.140
where it looks like all the
limbs are going back that way?

00:52:11.140 --> 00:52:14.060
Well, actually how that started,
it was a Stanley Chin creation.

00:52:14.060 --> 00:52:17.580
And when Jack Sustic got it, it
had that wonderful curving trunk,

00:52:17.580 --> 00:52:20.650
remember that, but all
the limbs were like this,

00:52:20.650 --> 00:52:23.230
so they're like a little triangle.

00:52:23.230 --> 00:52:25.050
And Jack thought, "How could
I make this more interesting?

00:52:25.050 --> 00:52:27.000
I can make the limbs go this way."

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:30.080
And he did it by wiring them
so that they'd all go that way.

00:52:30.080 --> 00:52:32.940
And you get that breathtaking
effect.

00:52:32.940 --> 00:52:36.530
The other thing to do
is what's called "clip

00:52:36.530 --> 00:52:39.620
and grow" that's more
typically used by the Chinese

00:52:39.620 --> 00:52:43.200
so that the trees are
trimmed, as opposed to wired.

00:52:43.200 --> 00:52:44.860
And the way I think about penjing

00:52:44.860 --> 00:52:46.890
versus bonsai is it's
like calligraphy.

00:52:46.890 --> 00:52:49.540
You know, if you have block
print, you can read the sentence,

00:52:49.540 --> 00:52:53.450
but if you have it in copper plate,
you can also read the sentence.

00:52:53.450 --> 00:52:54.770
So it's -- you know, they're not --

00:52:54.770 --> 00:52:56.780
they're in the same
bracket that way,

00:52:56.780 --> 00:52:59.260
just sort of different
ways of treating it.

00:52:59.260 --> 00:53:02.380
And it's similarly with
the training, you know,

00:53:02.380 --> 00:53:04.750
they use the wires in Japan and
here in the States, but then clip

00:53:04.750 --> 00:53:06.050
and grow is more typical in China.

