00:53:31.460 --> 00:53:33.770
I just asked that the other
day when I was out there,

00:53:33.770 --> 00:53:37.410
because when you see them, some of
them have what looks like teabags

00:53:37.410 --> 00:53:42.180
on their bases, other ones have
pellets, others have nothing.

00:53:42.180 --> 00:53:47.660
And so they use particular
planting material for some trees

00:53:47.660 --> 00:53:51.250
that is enough nutrients
for the tree.

00:53:51.250 --> 00:53:53.320
Others need different supplements.

00:53:53.320 --> 00:53:56.670
And so it really depends
on the type of tree,

00:53:56.670 --> 00:53:58.550
and makes all the difference
actually.

00:53:58.550 --> 00:54:01.910
Because when you think about it,
if you have just this much space

00:54:01.910 --> 00:54:06.820 position:56%
to get all your nutrients as opposed
to acres, it's really essential

00:54:06.820 --> 00:54:08.330
that you get the right mix.

00:54:08.330 --> 00:54:10.570
So it varies from variety
to variety.

00:54:10.570 --> 00:54:12.800
Great question; yes, thank you.

00:54:12.800 --> 00:54:16.660
&gt;&gt; Yes. I can just add to that
